  "section_name": "Investment Recommendation & Outlook",
  "text": "Alphabet's fundamental trajectory supports constructive long-term views. Q4 2025 revenue reached $113.9 billion, representing 11.29% year-over-year growth that accelerated from prior quarters, indicating strengthening demand across core business segments. Profitability remained exceptional with gross margin at 59.82%, operating margin at 31.61%, and net margin at 30.25%. Free cash flow generation was robust at a 21.56% margin, and the balance sheet exhibited strong liquidity with a current ratio of 2.01 and conservative leverage at a 0.17 debt-to-equity ratio. R&D investment intensity remained elevated at 16.31% of revenue, positioning the company to compete in AI and cloud infrastructure markets.",
